%text \[ 1 +2x+3x^2 = 0 \] has no real roots. Which means, that \underline\text{\[1+2x+3x^2 \] can't be factorized}.
Hence, let us try a different approach.
% \begin{align} \text{Let }5x - 2 &= A\cdot\frac{d}{dx}(1+2x+3x^2) + B \\ &= A\cdot(6x+2) +B = 6A\cdot x + (2A + B) \\ \implies 6A &= 5 \text{ or } A = \frac{5}{6} \\ \text{and }2A + B &= -2 \implies B = -2 - 2\cdot \left(\frac{5}{6}\right) = -\frac{11}{3} \end{align}
